 @bananawarriorwootwoot  Good on you! I have great respect for immigrants to America that seek a better life and contribute to the betterment of our society. Modern day immigrants are generally some of the hardest working and most respectful people in this country. Americans so often forget that we are a nation of immigrants. It's incredibly easy for a natural-born American to take this country for granted, feel entitled and think that they are owed something for the mere fact that they were born here. It's been my experience that immigrants have an appreciation for this country because of their perspective from the country which they emigrated from. This world owes you nothing, you get only what you put in. Sadly, that is lost on many natural-born Americans.

It's only by luck and circumstance that someone happens to be born here. It's too easily overlooked that one of your ancestors decided to risk it all and travel to a foreign land in search of a better life. Excluding Native Americans, that is essentially how every natural-born citizen got here. Who are we to deny someone that is trying to better theirs and their families lives? It's far too hypocritical a stance for me.

I hope that you don't have too hard of a time dealing with future immigration issues. I also hope that you can become a naturalized citizen, if you so desire. Keep up the good work. Take care and be well. 🇺🇸
